results.title: Survival of the fittest
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Small Business”
Why small businesses grow or die - an investigation based on interviews with the principals of a number of firms, ranging from a one-man factory that is doing well to a dynamic enterprise. Gives examples of the special problems of those who inherit a family firm. Small firms are especially vulnerable but sometimes compensate with special satisfactions.

results.title: The Hard sell
results.creator_credit: Paul Ellis, Tony Matthews and BBC-TV
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Small Business”.
How can the smaller firm make money from better marketing? Interviews with business and marketing experts establish several valuable selling approaches. Stresses the importance of making the right product, and keeping production and sales in step. Includes advice on both home and export sales. NB: Dated and “politically incorrect” in some segments.

results.title: Finance in the balance
results.creator_credit: Paul Ellis, Tony Matthews and BBC-TV
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Small Business”.
The financial problems of the smaller firm, including getting a bank loan, what the bank looks for before giving financial support, and how a businessman can control finances. Also examines some of the most common causes of mortality in small companies.

results.title: Oxy Acetylene Welding
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Skills”.
Explains the process of welding; cutting, braising, bronze-welding and heating, and demonstrates exercises to practice to acquire the skills necessary to become a competent welder. Also demonstrates correct and safe procedures to follow when closing down.

results.title: Oxy Acetylene Cutting
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Skills”.
Describes a variety of uses and procedures for oxy welding cutting. These include 1) Safety Rules 20 Equipment 3) Equipment Safety 4) Care and Maintenance of Equipment 6) Closing Down.

results.title: Knockbacks
results.brief_description:
Episode number 6 of Series “Six of the best”.
Introduces issues about employers and the workplace, casual work and family relationships. Antoni finds a short lived labouring job; Brian walks off his job after an argument with the foreman; Sal is still looking for work in the face of lack of family understanding and Brian’s father is retrenched.

results.title: Six of the best
results.brief_description: This series looks at issues which affect young adults in their daily life. Six teenagers, Brian, Antoni, Carl, Paula, Sally and Theresa deal with such problems as employment, school and relationships. Passing out, Early starters, Pay day, Pairing off, Shooting through, and Knockbacks.

results.title: Shooting through
results.brief_description:
Episode number 5 of Series “Six of the best”.
Introduces issues concerned with welfare funding, job hunting and the responsibility of employers. Antoni loses his job at the service station and Sal continues to look for secretarial work, but with no success. Founding is cut for the drop in centre.

results.title: Pairing off
results.brief_description:
Episode number 4 of Series “Six of the best”.
Introduces issues concerned with living away from home, multicultural differences and male and female relationships. Carl and Theresa move in together and their Italian parents cannot accept this. Paula goes out with Gary who has a cynical approach to business and personal relationships.
